 469:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //! @details    This function writes the logic levels given by @a data_p at
 470:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 the of bus pins. The provided @a data_p must be relative
 471:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 to the bus first pin. If the bus mode is set to
 472:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 @ref PinMode::OUTPUT_PUSH_PULL, the pin outputs
 473:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 will be set to @ref LogicLevel::LOW or
 474:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 @ref LogicLevel::HIGH according to the bit value in
 475:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 @a data_p.
 476:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //! @warning    It is recommended to use this function only when the bus
 477:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 mode is set to @ref PinMode::OUTPUT_PUSH_PULL,
 478:funsape/peripheral/gpioBus.hpp ****     //!                 otherwise, the mode of some pins will be changed to
